{
  "name": "Muscle Soreness Tracker",
  "short_name": "Soreness",
  "description": "A simple PWA to track muscle soreness throughout the week.",
  "start_url": ".",
  "display": "standalone",
  "background_color": "#ffffff",
  "theme_color": "#ffffff",
  "icons": [
    {
      "src": "icons/icon192.png",
      "sizes": "192x192",
      "type": "image/png",
      "purpose": "any maskable" 
    },
    {
      "src": "icons/icon512.png",
      "sizes": "512x512",
      "type": "image/png",
       "purpose": "any maskable"
    }
  ]
}
```
* **`name` / `short_name`:** How the app appears.
* **`start_url`:** The page that loads when the app starts (`.` means the current directory, i.e., `index.html`).
* **`display: standalone`:** Makes it look like a native app (no browser address bar).
* **`background_color` / `theme_color`:** Used for the splash screen and browser UI theming.
* **`icons`:** Crucial for the home screen icon. You need to create actual PNG icons (e.g., 192x192 and 512x512 pixels) and update the `src` paths. The `purpose: "any maskable"` helps ensure the icon looks good on different Android shap
